                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d959">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13795.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-16T10:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Resulting from conference of General González with the First Chief, the latter
                    has made another proposition. He offers to resign his military command to
                    General González; proposes that Villa resign his to Gutiérrez, and that both
                    himself and Villa retire to Havana by the 25th; the Convention to reassemble in
                    Mexico City and elect a Provisional President for the entire pre-constitutional
                    period; and that Gutiérrez and González shall then deliver to the new President
                    their respective forces.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
